<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="thirsty-adj">thirsty <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'θɜːsti/    美 /'θɜːrsti/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>渴的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Salty food makes you thirsty.
吃咸的食物会使你口渴。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>缺水的；干旱的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>thirsty fields
干旱的田地</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>渴求的；渴望的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Printing answered a need because people were <strong>thirsty for</strong> knowledge.
人们渴求知识，印刷术满足了这一需求。</p><footer>外研⑧ – 2</footer></div></div>